  "title": "Sustained Neural Representations of Personally Familiar People and Places During Cued Recall",
  "description": "This dataset contains magnetoencephalography (MEG) data from a cued recall task designed to investigate sustained neural representations of personally familiar people and places. Participants were cued to recall specific individuals and locations while neural activity was recorded, enabling investigation of how the brain maintains and represents autobiographical memories and social knowledge during deliberate retrieval.",
